Modifications from upstream:
  - include paths updated for local (../common.xml, ../humanoid_modified.xml)
  - <option timestep="0.005"/> added (dm_control humanoid default; the MJPC
    planner sets physics dt programmatically via agent_timestep, but our Python
    pipeline uses sim_dt * n_substeps = ctrl_dt, so an explicit timestep is
    required). With n_substeps=3 in HumanoidStandDynamics this gives
    ctrl_dt=0.015 s, matching MJPC's agent_timestep.
  - <custom> planner settings block removed — carried in PROPOSAL_CONFIGS
    instead (P=3, N=10, sigma=0.125, horizon=0.35 s -> 23 planner steps, cubic).
    Upstream had: agent_horizon=0.35, agent_timestep=0.015,
    sampling_spline_points=3, sampling_exploration=0.05, residual_Height Goal
    param = 1.4 (min 0.0, max 1.5); we use 1.4 as the hard-coded height goal in
    HumanoidStandDynamics.
  - <user> cost sensors removed — residual computed in
    HumanoidStandDynamics.cost_function (5 terms, matches current stand.cc).
  - <sensor> block trimmed to the subtreelinvel and subtreecom declarations
    required to populate data.subtree_linvel / data.subtree_com; other MJPC
    estimator/trace sensors are irrelevant to the residual.
-->
<mujoco model="Humanoid Stand">
  <include file="../common.xml"/>
  <include file="../humanoid_modified.xml"/>

  <size memory="400K"/>
  <option timestep="0.005"/>

  <sensor>
    <subtreelinvel name="torso_subtreelinvel" body="torso"/>
    <subtreecom    name="torso_subtreecom"    body="torso"/>
  </sensor>
</mujoco>
